title: AHS: 1984 Ending Explained and Episode 9 Breakdown! "Final Girl"
author: Think Story
comment: Just want to extend a huge THANK YOU for those of you who watched my AHS breakdowns this season. Hope you'll stick around I plan to do a bunch of other shows and movies! RIP Bertie 🔪
This season finale had a more sentimental and heartwarming feeling at the end of the episode than most other seasons.

Brooke's survival was my only problem. We didn't see her getting rescued so I genuinely believed her soul was saved by satan and that's why she kept her youth, but at least Emma Roberts finally survived a season.
seemed like a really short season or is it just me?

I absolutely loved this episode and this season, but this doesn’t feel like the ending to me, nothing was explained, it was just like “well this is how they’re doing, bye”. Definitely looking forward for your version of ending!
description:
American Horror Story: 1984 has come to an end and I'm here to breakdown the last episode, episode 9 "Final Girl" reviewing theories, details you missed and how it ties into the rest of the season.
